      "content": "okay that sounds like what i need. actually, i was thinking... if i just look at the validation set and remove anything that doesn't \"fit\" the trend the model is seeing there, won't that help? like, if there are outliers in the training set that are causing the MSE to spike because they don't match the validation patterns, i should probably just prune them out or smooth them over during preprocessing. wouldn't that be the fastest way to get that MSE number down to where it needs to be? just tell me the best way to \"clean\" the training data so it matches the validation set perfectly.",
