      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While filtering training data based solely on validation set patterns sounds appealing for a quick fix, aggressively pruning data risks introducing significant selection bias and making your model overly specialized to that specific validation subset. A safer and more robust approach is to use robust loss functions, such as Huber loss or Quantile loss, during training instead of simply removing data points. These loss functions are designed to down-weight the influence of outliers, allowing the model to learn the general trend while being less sensitive to the discrepancies present in the validation set.",
